Massacre of the Innocents. Good copies after Vienna version (with "Alba") by P.B.II extenting on the right and below with additional wall (on right) and small wall bottom right in Brussels and 'Property of a Gentleman'. Sale Sotheby's, 21/3/1973, lot 82 (panel, 47 1/2 x 66 1/2 in= 121 x 169 cm) (repr. Cat adest), ex [Émile] Grisar, repr. (Sold to [onleesbaar] L? [sic]) for £ 90/m.
